OL,3,CBloody Sunday family felt 'anxious and
OL,4,Cwary' after menacing message
OL,6,FThe family of a Bloody Sunday victim
OL,7,Fhave welcomed a six-month sentence
OL,8,Fgiven to a man convicted of sending a
OL,9,Fmenacing message to them during the
OL,10,FSoldier F trial.
OL,12,FDean Portis faced prosecution over a
OL,13,Fsocial media posting seen by the three
OL,14,Fbrothers of William McKinney, one of
OL,15,Fthose shot dead by the army in
OL,16,FLondonderry in 1972.
OL,18,FOn Wednesday, the 42-year-old was
OL,19,Fjailed and also banned from
OL,20,Fintimidating or harassing them as part
OL,21,Fof a two-year restraining order.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/9
